SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PART V, LINE 4 - THE BENEFICIAL INTEREST IN ASSETS HELD BY THE COMMUNITY FOUNDATION ARE DESIGNATED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS TO ESTABLISH FUNDS ON A LONG-TERM BASIS FOR PROGRAM SERVICES. THIS IS THE INTENDED USE OF THE ORGANIZATION'S ENDOWMENT FUNDS.
PART X, LINE 1 (2) - OTHER LIABILITIES: LEASE PAYABLE FOR LEASED OFFICE SPACE $49,384.

PART X, LINE 2 - FINANCIAL FOOTNOTE: THE ORGANIZATION IS A CHARITABLE ORGANIZATION UNDER SECTION 501 (C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE, AND THUS IS EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAXES. GIFTS, GRANTS AND BEQUESTS ARE DEDUCTIBLE BY DONORS WITHIN LIMITATIONS OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. THE ORGANIZATION IS SUBJECT TO A TAX ON INCOME FROM ANY UNRELATED ACTIVITIES. NO UNRELATED ACTIVITIES WERE IDENTIFIED IN THE CURRENT YEAR. THE ORGANIZATION CONTINUALLY EVALUATES ITS TAX POSITIONS, CHANGES IN TAX LAWS, AND NEW AUTHORITATIVE RULINGS FOR POTENTIAL IMPLICATIONS TO ITS TAX STATUS.
PART XII, LINE 2D - EXPENSE AMOUNTS INCLUDED IN FINANCIALS - OTHER CHANGES IN BENEFICIAL INTEREST $11,425.

PROCEDURES FOR MONITORING THE USE OF GRANT FUNDS: THE ORGANIZATION REQUIRES PROOF OF IRS DETERMINATION AND USES THE IRS.GOV TO ENDURE THAT THE STATUS, ADDRESS, AND OTHER INFORMATION ON A POTENTIAL GRANTEE IS CORRECT BEFORE THEY ARE APPROVED FOR A GRANT. THIS PROCESS IS USED TO ENSURE THAT THE ORGANIZATION IS ONLY GIVING GRANTS TO QUALIFIED CHARITIES. GRANTEES SUBMIT A GRANT RECAP FORM OUTLINING HOW THE GRANT WAS USED AND HOW MANY PEOPLE WERE SERVED. PHONE AND/OR SITE VISITS, AND EXIT INTERVIEWS ARE DONE BY THE ORGANIZATION'S GRANT COMMITTEE.
ALL OTHER ACCOMPLISHMENTS: PROVIDE REFERRAL SERVICES TO NUMEROUS PARENTS SEEKING CHILD CARE AND PROVIDE ASSISTANCE AND TRAINING TO SEVERAL PROVIDERS.

ReasonableCauseExplanation.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAD FILED IRS FORM 8868 TO FILE AN EXTENSION FOR FILING THE 2022 FORM 990. IN ORDER TO REDUCE THE ANNUAL FINANCIAL AUDIT COSTS FOR THE 2022 FINANCIAL AUDIT, THE 2022 FORM 990 WAS PREPARED IN-HOUSE FOR THE FIRST TIME IN 2023, USING THE ONLINE IRS FORMS AVAILABLE ON THE IRS WEBSITE, IRS.GOV. ALL OF THE FORMS WERE COMPLETED AND IN A PDF FORMAT, AND WERE READY TO BE UPLOADED TO THE IRS WEBSITE PRIOR TO THE EXTENSION DEADLINE IN FILING THE FORM 990 AND ITS SUPPORTING SCHEDULES. HOWEVER, IT WAS BROUGHT TO OUR ATTENTION THAT THOSE IRS.GOV FORMS WERE NOT USABLE FOR FILING THE FORM 990 ONLINE VIA PDF FORMAT. INSTEAD, WE WERE NOTIFIED BY THE 990 IRS SUPPORT ONLINE HELP AT 1-877-829-5500, THAT WE HAD TO EXPEND $100-$200 IN PURCHASING AN ONLINE SOFTWARE PACKAGE, IN ORDER TO FILE THE FORM 990 AND SUPPORTING SCHEDULES. THEREFORE, WE UTILIZED THE VENDOR (FORM 990 ONLINE) TO REENTER ALL OF THE DATA ON THE FORMS OF THE 2022 FORM AND ITS SUPPORTING SCHEDULES A SECOND TIME, IN ORDER TO MEET THE REQUIREMENTS TO ENABLE US TO ELECTRONICALLY FILE THE FORM 990 FOR THE FIRST TIME IN-HOUSE, USING THIS REQUIRED SOFTWARE PACKAGE. WE WERE NOTIFIED BY THE 990 IRS SUPPORT HOTLINE THAT MAILING THE FORM 990 WAS NOT AN OPTION TO US. THEREFORE, WE ARE REQUESTING CONSIDERATION FOR A ONE-TIME ABATEMENT OF ANY LATE PENALTIES AND INTEREST IN FILING THE 2022 FORM 990 FOR OUR ORGANIZATION THIS YEAR. WE HAVE BEEN EDUCATED IN HOW THE ANNUAL FORM 990 MUST BE ELECTRONICALLY FILED USING AN IRS REQUIRED SOFTWARE VENDOR AT AN ADDITIONAL ANNUAL COST TO OUR ORGANIZATION, WHICH WE WERE PREVIOUSLY UNAWARE OF THIS IRS FILING REQUIREMENT. THANK YOU FOR OUR CONSIDERATION OF THIS REQUEST.
